Immigration policy became a central tool for stratifying rights and enforcing ideological conformity. The State Department halted medical visas for children from Gaza after a far-right influencer falsely portrayed them as a security threat, cutting off life-saving treatment based on conspiracy rather than evidence. The administration announced that more than 6,000 student visas had been revoked, citing crime and \'93support for terrorism\'94 without providing detailed proof. U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services issued a new policy calling for more subjective judgments of \'93good moral character\'94 in citizenship applications. At the same time, the State Department and DHS rolled out \'93continuous vetting\'94 for all 55 million visa holders, including social media monitoring for \'93anti-American\'94 activity, and expanded social media screening for immigration applicants. Status became contingent on perceived loyalty.\
